cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with image quality assessment, which is a task related to computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses deep neural networks and adversarial learning, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper involves regression, which is a common technique in neural networks, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves implicit ranking relationships, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks for ranking tasks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
